b"@veefriends  Breakdown
The blue chip that doesn't get hyped
this project didn't start with great art (sorry Gary)
but what it starts with, or rather who"

b"Veefriends 1 originally dropped as a series of hand drawn characters of varying rarity and included many other special nfts with verying utilities like the gift goat (which guarantees physical and digital gifts) and even access tokens, promising Gary's time."
b"Gary's NFT collections has now branched into 3 parts which are intertwined\nVeefriends 1, Book Games, and Veefriends 2"

b'Book games now also serves a role in distributing the friends list (aka whitelist) For veefriends 2. Utility to be confirmed. Each BG nft gives a 26% chance of getting on the whitelist for VF2.\nVF1 holders get 1 free mint (+gas) per VF1.'
b'Recently veefriends partnered up with zerocool to auction the first trading card collection for veefriends. @zerocoolcards 22644 bids were placed, the clearing price was 2150.'
b"Veefriends to me looks like it will become its own Universe, like Marvel or DC. The stories will come with time, but that's where its heading. The art has been upgraded and the hints are there."

b'Veefriends 1 owners will likely own the equivalent of the first edition releases. The original drafts of the characters drawn by Garyvee himself.\nVeefriends 2 owners have the first official versions of the characters. As a collector this could mean alot in 10 years'

b'Currently the NFT market is filled with a lot of projects that are very similar. \nVeefriends is a breath of fresh air and takes a different approach to WEB3\nNot financial advice, DYOR. Different can mean better but it can mean worse as well.'

b'1/13\nMarch madness came a few days early this year here at VeeFriends. We dropped some major alpha on Series 2 and Series 1, had our latest collaboration with zerocool to launch the first ever VeeFriends Trading Cards, and our VeeCon Ticket Burn Sale is LIVE!'
b'VeeFriends Roundup (3/4-3/11): Series 2 Alpha, VeeFriends Trading Cards, VeeCon Ticket Burn Sale, and More! \xf0\x9f\xa7\xb5 https://t.co/kQ6YgZHcAB'

b'2/13\nVeeFriends Series 2 Alpha for Series 1 Holders:\nThis week, the highly anticipated question was answered\xe2\x80\x93\xe2\x80\x9cwhat is the Series 2 advantage VeeFriends Series 1 holders?\xe2\x80\x9d Every Series 1 holder will be able to claim for free (plus gas) a Series 2 NFT of their current character(s). https://t.co/tfaJBMrkK4'

b'3/13\nThese will be the most sought-after NFTs in the Series 2 collection and will not be available in the Friends List/General Public Mint of the Series 2 drop. To learn more about the Series 1 advantage for Series 2 check out our featured blog: https://t.co/wuMOf4rU88 https://t.co/sJe4UwE2qr'

b'5/13\nWith the launch of @zerocoolcards, a subsidiary of @Fanatics Collectible, we believe there is tremendous upside collabing with zerocool on the ground floor as their inaugural collection as they begin their journey as the premium trading card brand for culture.'

b'4/13\nVeeFriends x zerocool:\nSince the creation of VeeFriends, we have been passionate in adding trading cards as part of building the IP. The depth of the trading card scene is a major component of culture and shares parallels and similarities to the NFT space.'

b'7/13\n7-Day Only VeeCon Ticket Burn Sale! \xf0\x9f\x8e\x9f\nWe announced some exciting news for individuals who want to attend VeeCon. On 3/11 we announced a 7-day only VeeCon Ticket Burn Sale, while supplies last!'

b'6/13\nOn March 10th, our zerocool collaboration ended in a \xe2\x80\x9cblind dutch-auction\xe2\x80\x9d bidding format with over 22,000 bids and a clearing auction price of $2150. Thank you to everyone who participated and congratulations to the winners! https://t.co/k6RxnRITFo'

b'8/13\nThe burn sale will be from March 11th, 2022 @ 12:00 PM ET through March 18th and allow those who have the required amount of BOOK GAMES tokens to burn them in exchange for a VeeCon Ticket NFT at a sale price! \nLearn more: https://t.co/Op0T9X8J3b'

b'9/13\nNew @VeeCon Speaker Announcement:\nWe are excited to announce ten new speakers that will be joining us at VeeCon! We will be announcing more speakers in the coming weeks, check out our latest additions below: https://t.co/70DjbY7ejN'
